               <head>Works by ʿUbayd Zākānī, 12 items (a-l)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100085 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2002005579 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh86006866 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85121918">
                  <summary>Substantial fragment from a large compendious collection of muntakhab or selected humorous and moral poetry and refined prose works by the noted poet and satirist of late Ilkhanid Iran, based at the Muzaffarid court of Shiraz and thus senior contemporary of the famous 
                     <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658491.0x000001 person_56731778" role="aut">Shams al-Dīn Ḥāfiẓ</persName>, 
            <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658491.0x000001 viaf_311227306" role="aut">Khvājah ʿUbayd Zākānī</persName>(d. 772/1371), here named 
            <persName key="viaf_311227306" role="aut">Najm al-Dīn</persName>, and not, as specified by Rypka, 
            <persName key="viaf_311227306" role="aut">Niẓām al-Dīn</persName>. Volume not dated; datable to mid-sixteenth to mid-seventeenth centuries. Neat scribal nastaʿlīq. Limited annotations in margins. Stamped and Persian foliation. Lacking original binding. Binding, red half leather IOL covers, dated 8/8/[19]23. Folios bound, occasional lacunae; stains, cropped, warping and cockling, wormholes, later repairs, gauze overlay. Condition fair.
                  </summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1208-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="2v">ff. 1v-2v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1208a.</p>
                        <p>Preface by an unnamed compiler introducing a selection of fourteen works by the poet and satirist of Muzaffarid Shiraz, 
                <persName key="viaf_311227306" role="aut">ʿUbayd Zākānī</persName>(d. 772/1371), here named 
                <persName key="viaf_311227306" role="aut">Najm al-Dīn</persName>, and not, as specified by Rypka, 
                <persName key="viaf_311227306" role="aut">Niẓām al-Dīn</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>The present volume contains works numbering less than the quantity of fourteen specified here.</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                        <p>Earlier Persian foliation commences at 151.</p>
                        <p>The flyleaf before the first folio bears the ink transfer in reverse of an inscription found on f. 130v, indicating the latter has been bound in the wrong order.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_311227306">Najm al-Dīn ʿUbayd Zākānī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_311227306">نجم الدّين عبيد زاكانى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22932">Risālah dar taqrīr-i dībāchah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22932">رساله در تقرير ديباچه</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1208-item2">
                     <locus from="3r" to="4v">ff. 3r-4v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1208b.</p>
                        <p>Untitled abridged version of a manqabat to the 
                <persName key="viaf_97245226" role="subject">Prophet Muḥammad</persName>in the form of a tarkīb by the poet and satirist of Muzaffarid Shiraz, 
                <persName key="viaf_311227306" role="aut">ʿUbayd Zākānī</persName>(d. 772/1371).
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_311227306">ʿUbayd Zākānī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_311227306">عبيد زاكانى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1208-item3">
                     <locus from="5r" to="16r">ff. 5r-16r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1208c.</p>
                        <p>Moralistic treatise in refined prose and poetry by the poet and satirist of Muzaffarid Shiraz, 
                <persName key="viaf_311227306" role="aut">ʿUbayd Zākānī</persName>(d. 772/1371).
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_311227306">ʿUbayd Zākānī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_311227306">عبيد زاكانى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22934">Risālah-'i rīsh</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22934">رسالهٴ ريش</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1208-item4">
                     <locus from="17r" to="23r">ff. 17r-23r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1208d.</p>
                        <p>Collection of two tarjīʿband poems by the poet and satirist of Muzaffarid Shiraz, ʿUbayd Zākānī (d. 772/1371).</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName key="viaf_311227306" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">ʿUbayd Zākānī</persName>
                        <persName key="viaf_311227306" xml:lang="fa">عبيد زاكانى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22935">Kitāb al-tarjīʿ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22935">كتاب التّرجيع</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1208-item5">
                     <locus from="23r" to="41v">ff. 23r-41v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1208e.</p>
                        <p>Collection of narrative poetic compositions in various forms (mas̲navī, bayt, qiṭʿah, ghazal, rubāʿī) imitating or inspired by the works of other poets, written by the poet and satirist of Muzaffarid Shiraz, ʿUbayd Zākānī (d. 772/1371).</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName key="viaf_311227306" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">ʿUbayd Zākānī</persName>
                        <persName key="viaf_311227306" xml:lang="fa">عبيد زاكانى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22936">Kitāb-i taz̤mīnāt</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22936">كتاب تضمينات</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="6" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1208-item6">
                     <locus from="41v" to="74v">ff. 41v-74v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1208f.</p>
                        <p>Collection of moralistic, picaresque, and bawdy tales in refined prose and poetry by the poet and satirist of Muzaffarid Shiraz, ʿUbayd Zākānī (d. 772/1371).</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_311227306">ʿUbayd Zākānī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_311227306">عبيد زاكانى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22937">Risālah-'i dilkushā</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22937">رسالهٴ دلكشا</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="7" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1208-item7">
                     <locus from="74v" to="89r">ff. 74v-89r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1208g.</p>
                        <p>Mystical treatise compiling responses to the correspondence and anecdotes of contemporary Sufis written by the poet and satirist of Muzaffarid Shiraz, ʿUbayd Zākānī (d. 772/1371).</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName key="viaf_311227306" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">ʿUbayd Zākānī</persName>
                        <persName key="viaf_311227306" xml:lang="fa">عبيد زاكانى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22938">Risālah-'i qalandarān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22938">رسالهٴ قلندران</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="8" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1208-item8">
                     <locus from="89r" to="94v">ff. 89r-94v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1208h.</p>
                        <p>Treatise on mystical terminology, also known as 
                <title key="work_22939">Risālah-'i taʿrīfāt</title>, intending to acquaint the youth of the day with the pronouncements of former literary and especially Sufi masters, clarifying their use of diction and style, by the poet and satirist of Muzaffarid Shiraz, ʿUbayd Zākānī (d. 772/1371).
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_311227306">ʿUbayd Zākānī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_311227306">عبيد زاكانى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22939">Dah faṣl</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22939">ده فصل</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="9" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1208-item9">
                     <locus from="95r" to="103r">ff. 95r-103r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1208i.</p>
                        <p>Ethical treatise collecting moral dicta in the form of a 
                <title key="work_22940">vaṣīyat</title>or last will and testament attributed to 
                <persName key="viaf_108159964" role="att">Aflātūn</persName>or 
                <persName key="viaf_108159964" role="att">Plato</persName>, who supposedly composed it for the instruction of his student 
                <persName key="viaf_7524651" role="dte">Arisṭū</persName>or 
                <persName key="viaf_7524651" role="dte">Aristotle</persName>, subsequently translated from the Greek to Persian and appended to the 
                <title key="work_22940">Akhlāq-i Nāṣirī</title>by 
                <persName key="viaf_12392936" role="oth">Khvājah Naṣīr al-Dīn Ṭūsī</persName>, and here restyled by the poet and satirist of Muzaffarid Shiraz, ʿUbayd Zākānī (d. 772/1371), in 750/1349 (here incorrectly written 950/1543).
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_311227306">ʿUbayd Zākānī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_311227306">عبيد زاكانى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22940">Ṣad pand</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22940">صد پند</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="10" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1208-item10">
                     <locus from="103v" to="120v">ff. 103v-120v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1208j.  </p>
                        <p>Treatise on divination based on alphanumerical values devised by the poet and satirist of Muzaffarid Shiraz, ʿUbayd Zākānī (d. 772/1371).</p>
                        <p>The work is divided into twelve sections termed bāb, each corresponding to signs of the zodiac.</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_311227306">ʿUbayd Zākānī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_311227306">عبيد زاكانى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22941">Fāʾl'nāmah-'i burūj</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22941">فأل نامهٴ بروج</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="11" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1208-item11">
                     <locus from="121r" to="124r">ff. 121r-124r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1208k.  </p>
                        <p>Untitled manual of divination based on a chart (f. 121r) listing the names of common and mythical birds, written in the form of quatrains, attributable to the poet and satirist of Muzaffarid Shiraz, ʿUbayd Zākānī (d. 772/1371).</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <author/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="12" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1208-item12">
                     <locus from="124v" to="129v">ff. 124v-129v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1208(l).  </p>
                        <p>Untitled manual of divination based on a chart (f. 121r) listing the names of common and mythical wild beasts or vuḥūsh, written in the form of quatrains, attributable to the poet and satirist of Muzaffarid Shiraz, ʿUbayd Zākānī (d. 772/1371).</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_311227306">ʿUbayd Zākānī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_311227306">عبيد زاكانى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
